{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17588780","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17588780"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T09:10:51+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T09:10:51+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15170"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15170","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15170"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.44,0.02,0,0.51,0.02]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7861"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66464"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7861","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7861"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15170"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51915"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"3"},{"type":"tags","id":"31"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"1367"},{"type":"tags","id":"2058"},{"type":"tags","id":"4937"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"8137"},{"type":"tags","id":"9419"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19162"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19165"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22223"},{"type":"contributions","id":"35123"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66464","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/66464"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 65-year-old man who has worked outdoors as a farmer for 40 years presents with a non-healing ulcerated lesion on his lower lip (Image). He has a 5 pack-year smoking history and drinks two cans of beer a day. The lesion is excised and histologically shown to be a squamous cell carcinoma.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely cause?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Cigarette smoking","Alcohol consumption","Leukoplakia","Ultraviolet radiation","Lichen planus"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe oral cavity is a relatively common site for the development of cancers, where 90% of cases being squamous cell carcinoma (SCC). Squamous cell carcinoma can present in various ways, most typically being ulcerated lesions, but also as exophytic masses or indurated plaques. \u003Cstrong\u003EUltraviolet radiation\u003C/strong\u003E is a major risk factor, particularly for lip cancer, which is why outdoor workers are at increased risk.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOther important causes for SCC of the lip include smoking, alcohol, betel nut chewing and human papilloma virus (HPV). In this particular case, the patient\u0027s smoking and alcohol consumption are much lesser risk factor compared to his time spent outdoors in the sun.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWith regards to other cancers within the oral cavity, the premalignant conditions as leucoplakia, proliferative verrucous leukoplakia, erythroplasia, oral lichen planus, and oral submucous fibrosis are risk factors to be considered.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Squamous cell carcinoma accounts for over 90% of head and neck cancers and the oral cavity is a common site for squamous cell carcinoma","Ultraviolet radiation exposure is a major risk factor for squamous cell carcinoma of the lip"],"references":["Dreyfuss I, Kamath P, Frech F, Hernandez L, Nouri K. Squamous cell carcinoma: 2021 updated review of treatment. Dermatol Ther. 2022 Apr;35(4):e15308. doi: 10.1111/dth.15308. Epub 2022 Jan 17. PMID: 34997811.","Combalia A, Carrera C. Squamous Cell Carcinoma: An Update on Diagnosis and Treatment. Dermatol Pract Concept. 2020 Jun 29;10(3):e2020066. doi: 10.5826/dpc.1003a66. PMID: 32642314; PMCID: PMC7319751.","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51915"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15170"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"21268"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"21268","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21268"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/n4FxHs3p7VkpsW8Hk93TsANZZd3AMR.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/n4FxHs3p7VkpsW8Hk93TsANZZd3AMR.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":1500,"height":969}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51915","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/51915"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-30T12:45:25+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-28T19:46:33+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7861"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66464"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"3","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/3"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\uddf4","name":"Dermatology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:42+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"31","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/31"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf97","name":"Oncology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:45+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"m